OL,7,FTalking about answering that demand,
OL,8,FDr Lyons added: "First of all, we need
OL,9,Fto ensure that we prioritise those in
OL,10,Fmost need. And that's not always easy
OL,11,Fbecause we work on the information
OL,12,Fthat we're given. It's perhaps working
OL,13,Fin different ways. I'm working with
OL,14,Fpartners across local authorities in
OL,15,Feducation and with the voluntary
OL,16,Fsector and also being really clear
OL,17,Fwith individuals, their families, what
OL,18,Fwe can do and what we can't do.J"And
OL,19,Fat times handing patients back, you
OL,20,Fknow, sharing the load in the care
OL,21,Fwith colleagues in primary and
OL,22,Fcommunity services.J"It's really
OL,23,Fdifficult. And I suspect those people
OL,24,Fwho are finding it the most difficult
OL,25,Fare those who are just waiting,
OL,26,Fwaiting to understand what's happening
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/12
