OL,5,Cdouble
OL,7,FHe explained: "Of course if we are
OL,8,Foffered more money, we could say,
OL,9,Fthank you very much, but I don't think
OL,10,Fthis is actually a matter of money.
OL,11,FThis is a matter of finding the right
OL,12,Fskilled staff who when this challenge
OL,13,Fis nationwide, it's really difficult
OL,14,Fto recruit. It's encouraging people to
OL,15,Fwork differently and that takes time.
OL,16,FAnd it's also working to ensure that
OL,17,Fthe expectations of people are
OL,18,Ffulfilled.J"So yes, money is a part,
OL,19,Fbut perhaps a small part of the
OL,20,Fcurrent challenge."JAsked why there
OL,21,Fhad been such a growth in demand for
OL,22,Fservices, Dr Lyons said the answer is
OL,23,Fnot completely clear.
