OL,7,FHe explained: "There's been much
OL,8,Fdebate in the professional journals,
OL,9,Fmuch discussion at conferences, loads
OL,10,Fof ideas and proposals put forward as
OL,11,Fto why it might be. And there's been
OL,12,Fno clear answer that convinces me we
OL,13,Ffully understand it. I suspect it's a
OL,14,Fcombination of factors, but
OL,15,Fparticularly profound is that increase
OL,16,Fbetween the numbers we saw before the
OL,17,Fpandemic and the numbers that we're
OL,18,Fseeing after.J"I think we'd all
OL,19,Frecognize that society has changed in
OL,20,Fa way perhaps that we're only just
OL,21,Fbeginning to understand."
